html:
393 U.S. 86

89 S.Ct. 259

21 L.Ed.2d 218

Thomas Rogers LICHTEN et al.
v.
State of TEXAS.

No. 414.

Supreme Court of the United States

October 28, 1968

Rehearing Denied Dec. 9, 1968.

See 393 U.S. 992, 89 S.Ct. 443.

Chris Dixie, for appellants.

Crawford C. Martin, Atty. Gen. of Texas, Nola White, First Asst. Atty. Gen., A. J. Carubbi, Jr., Executive Asst. Atty. Gen., and Hawthorne Phillips, Gilbert J. Pena and Allo B. Crow, Jr., Asst. Attys. Gen., for appellee.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

2

Mr. Justice HARLAN is of the opinion that probable jurisdiction should be noted and the case set for argument.
